title: Explicit logrotate Execution
id: 57f495c9-d42d-42ce-81ca-3a795870747a
status: experimental
description: Detects logrotate commands being explicitly executed.  This is uncommon as logs are typically configured to rotate on a schedule; this technique has been utilized to kick off malicious binaries.
references:
    - https://support.scythe.io/knowledge/empower-logrotate
    - https://linux.die.net/man/8/logrotate
tags:
    - attack.execution
    - attack.t1059.004
author: Tyler Casey @1qazCasey, @scythe_io
date: 2024/10/03
logsource:
    category: process_creation
    product: linux
detection:
    selection:
        CommandLine|contains: ' logrotate '
    condition: selection
falsepositives:
    - Administrators forcing logs to rotate as part of work responsibilities.
level: low
